Nevada law (NRS 603A.340)
requires each business to establish a designated request address where Nevada
consumers may submit requests directing the business not to sell certain kinds
of personal information that the business has collected or will collect about
the consumer. A sale under Nevada law is the exchange of personal information
for monetary consideration by the business to a third party for the third party
to license or sell the personal information to other third parties. If you are
